1) рдЦрддрд░рдирд╛рдХ Attack-Vectors тАФ рдХреЙрдиреНрд╕реЗрдкреНрдЪреБрдЕрд▓ (рдХреНрдпрд╛ рдФрд░ рдХреНрдпреЛрдВ)

> рд╣рд░ рд╡реЗрдХреНрдЯрд░ рдЫреЛрдЯрд╛ рдмреЛрд▓реЗ рддреЛ тАЬphysical тЖТ visibility тЖТ exploitтАЭ рдХрд╛ shortcut рджреЗ рд╕рдХрддрд╛ рд╣реИред рдиреАрдЪреЗ рд╡рд╛рд▓реЗ рдкреЙрдЗрдВрдЯреНрд╕ рдХреИрд╕реЗ рдХрд░реЗрдВ рдирд╣реАрдВ рдмрддрд╛рдПрдВрдЧреЗ, рдмрд▓реНрдХрд┐ рдХрд┐рд╕ рддрд░рд╣ рдХрд╛рдо рдХрд░рддреЗ рд╣реИрдВ/рдХреНрдпрд╛ рд▓рдХреНрд╖рд┐рдд рдХрд░рддреЗ рд╣реИрдВ/рдХреМрди рд╕рд╛ рд╕рдВрдХреЗрдд рдорд┐рд▓реЗрдЧрд╛ рдпреЗ рдмрддрд╛рдПрдВрдЧреЗ:



1. Copper tap / inductive tap (passive sniffing)

рдХреНрдпрд╛: рдХреЗрдмрд▓ рдХреЗ рдХрд┐рдирд╛рд░реЗ рд╕реЗ рд╕рд┐рдЧреНрдирд▓ рдХрд╛ non-intrusive copy рд▓реЗрдирд╛ (physical contact рдпрд╛ clamp рдХреЗ рдЬрд░рд┐рдП)ред

рдХреНрдпреЛрдВ рдЦрддрд░рдирд╛рдХ: рдмрд┐рдирд╛ рдбрд╛рдЙрдирдЯрд╛рдЗрдо рдХреЗ traffic copy рд╕рдВрднрд╡; cleartext рдкреНрд░реЛрдЯреЛрдХреЙрд▓ рдореЗрдВ credentials рдорд┐рд▓ рд╕рдХрддреЗ рд╣реИрдВред

рд╕рдВрдХреЗрдд: рдЕрдЪрд╛рдирдХ duplicate frames, unexplained MAC visibility, intermittent packet anomaliesред

Defence: locked patch panels, port security, link-layer monitoringред (рджреЗрдЦрдиреЗ рдХреЗ рд▓рд┐рдП network telemetry рдЬрд░реВрд░реА)ред



2. Fiber optic bending / optical splitting

рдХреНрдпрд╛: fiber рдХреЛ micro-bend рдХрд░ рдХреЗ light leak/collect рдХрд░рдирд╛ рдпрд╛ optical splitter рд▓рдЧрд╛рдХрд░ copy рд▓реЗрдирд╛ред

рдХреНрдпреЛрдВ рдЦрддрд░рдирд╛рдХ: рд▓реЛрдЧ рд╕рдордЭрддреЗ рд╣реИрдВ fiber рд╕реБрд░рдХреНрд╖рд┐рдд рд╣реИ тАФ рдкрд░ bend/split techniques рд╕реЗ data leakage рд╣реЛ рд╕рдХрддрд╛ рд╣реИред

рд╕рдВрдХреЗрдд: optical power loss/attenuation, unexpected BER (bit error rate) changes, unplanned OTDR anomalies.

Defence: OTDR monitoring, physical protection of fiber runs, fiber-path inventory and CCTV for critical ducts. 



3. Rogue patch / hidden drop / unauthorized jack

рдХреНрдпрд╛: рдПрдХ unauthorized cable/jack/patch panel рдЬреЛ internal network рддрдХ рд╕реАрдзреЗ рдкрд╣реБрдВрдЪ рджреЗрддрд╛ рд╣реИред

рдХреНрдпреЛрдВ рдЦрддрд░рдирд╛рдХ: attacker physical access рдорд┐рд▓рдиреЗ рдкрд░ persistent foothold рдмрдирд╛ рд╕рдХрддрд╛ рд╣реИред

рд╕рдВрдХреЗрдд: wall-jack live but not in inventory, unexpected MAC on port, port flapping.

Defence: disable unused jacks, label+audit drops, tamper seals, port lockdown.



4. Malicious inline device (implanted hardware)

рдХреНрдпрд╛: compromised patch-cords, USB-Ethernet тАЬevil cableтАЭ рдпрд╛ tiny inline injectors рдЬреЛ traffic modify/redirect рдХрд░ рд╕рдХреЗрдВред

рдХреНрдпреЛрдВ рдЦрддрд░рдирд╛рдХ: hardware level compromise рдЕрдХреНрд╕рд░ bypasses software controls.

рд╕рдВрдХреЗрдд: changed device fingerprints, unexplained ARP changes, device model mismatch in inventory.

Defence: procure cabling from trusted vendors, inspect/scan new hardware, chain-of-custody for assets.



5. EMI / signal interference (DoS / degradation)

рдХреНрдпрд╛: intentional electromagnetic interference рдпрд╛ power-line coupling рд╕реЗ link degrade рдХрд░рдирд╛ред

рдХреНрдпреЛрдВ рдЦрддрд░рдирд╛рдХ: availability impact, packet loss causing failover or fallback to less-secure channels.

рд╕рдВрдХреЗрдд: sudden link errors, CRCs, degraded throughput.

Defence: shielded cabling where required, separate power/cable trays, environmental monitoring.




> рдЗрди vectors рдХреЗ рд╡реИрдЬреНрдЮрд╛рдирд┐рдХ рдФрд░ рдЕрдиреБрд╕рдВрдзрд╛рди-рд╕реНрддрд░ рдХреЗ рдХрд╛рдореЛрдВ рдкрд░ literature рдореМрдЬреВрдж рд╣реИ тАФ fiber tapping рдкрд░ technical рдкреЗрдкрд░ рдФрд░ commercial advisories рд╣реИрдВ рдЬрд┐рдиреНрд╣реЗрдВ defenders рдкрдврд╝реЗрдВред 




---

2) Indicators тАФ рдХреИрд╕реЗ detect рдХрд░реЗрдВ (рдЙрдЪреНрдЪ-рд╕реНрддрд░реАрдп) ЁЯФО

Optical power fluctuations рдпрд╛ OTDR anomalies (fiber). 

Switch logs: unexpected MAC addresses on static ports, port flapping, sudden broadcast surges.

Physical signs: tamper marks, non-standard cable ties, unlabeled drops.

Network telemetry: NetFlow spikes, multiple peers receiving identical frames (indicative of broadcast tap).

Long-term: unexplained lateral authentication failures, unknown hosts in VLAN.


(рдЗрди рд╕рдВрдХреЗрддреЛрдВ рдХреЛ SIEM/NSM/flow-collectors рдХреЗ alerts рд╕реЗ correlate рдХрд░рдирд╛ best practice рд╣реИ тАФ Zeek/Suricata рдЬреИрд╕реЗ NSM/IDS tools defenders use рдХрд░рддреЗ рд╣реИрдВ)ред 


---

3) Defence & Hardening тАФ рдХреНрдпрд╛ рд▓рд╛рдЧреВ рдХрд░реЗрдВ (рдкреНрд░реИрдХреНрдЯрд┐рдХрд▓ рдкрд░ non-operational) ЁЯЫбя╕П

Physical: Lock patch rooms/ID-control for contractors, tamper seals on panels, CCTV on critical runs, strict asset tagging.

Network: Replace hubs with managed switches, enable port security (MAC limiting, sticky MAC), enforce 802.1X where possible.

Fiber: OTDR baselines, continuous optical power monitoring, route diversity for critical links. 

Process: Change control for cable work, background checks for cabling vendors, documented chain-of-custody.

Detection: Deploy NSM (Zeek), IDS (Suricata/Snort), centralize logs into SIEM, netflow + PCAP retention policy for forensic windows. 



---

4) "Tools" тАФ рдирд╛рдо рдФрд░ рд░реЛрд▓ (рдХрд┐рд╕реЗ рдХрд╣рд╛рдБ рдкреНрд░рдпреЛрдЧ рдХрд░реЗрдВ тАФ рдХреЗрд╡рд▓ defensive / lab) ЁЯз░

> рдореИрдВ рдпрд╣рд╛рдБ tools рдХреЗ рдирд╛рдо рджреВрдБрдЧрд╛ рддрд╛рдХрд┐ рдЖрдк рдЙрдиреНрд╣реЗрдВ рд╕реАрдЦреЛ тАФ рдкрд░ live рдиреЗрдЯрд╡рд░реНрдХ рдкрд░ unauthorized use рдирд╛ рдХрд░реЛред рдкреНрд░рдпреЛрдЧ рдХреЗрд╡рд▓ lab/authorization рдХреЗ рд╕рд╛рдеред



Physical / Cabling

Fluke Networks DSX / Versiv family тАФ cable certification & troubleshooting (industry standard for copper/fiber). 


Network Monitoring / NSM / IDS

Zeek (Bro) тАФ passive network analysis / rich logs for defenders. 

Suricata / Snort тАФ signature and anomaly detection. 


Learning / Lab platforms (legal, hands-on)

OffSec (PEN-200 / OSCP family) тАФ rigorous offensive skills in isolated labs. 

TryHackMe тАФ guided paths from beginnerтЖТredteam with browser labs. 

Hack The Box тАФ advanced CTF style labs & pro labs. 

SANS courses for enterprise pen-testing / advanced red-team (defensive & offensive balance). 



---

5) рд╕реАрдЦрдиреЗ рдХрд╛ рдкреНрд░реЛ-рд░реЛрдбрдореИрдк (0 тЖТ Hero, рд╡рд╛рдпрд░рд┐рдВрдЧ + Layer-1 рдлреЛрдХрд╕) ЁЯОп

Stage A тАФ Fundamentals (0тАУ4 weeks)

рдиреЗрдЯрд╡рд░реНрдХ рдмреЗрд╕рд┐рдХреНрд╕: OSI, Ethernet, ARP, switching, VLANs.

рдХреЗрдмрд▓рд┐рдВрдЧ types: Cat5e/6/6a/7, fiber (single-mode vs multimode), connectors (LC/SC, RJ45).


Stage B тАФ Detection & Analysis (4тАУ12 weeks)

Packet analysis theory (Wireshark for analysis only) тАФ encrypted vs cleartext.

NSM basics: Zeek logs, Suricata alerts, NetFlow interpretation. 


Stage C тАФ Physical security & cable expertise (8тАУ16 weeks)

Cable certification tools (Fluke DSX) operation for installation acceptance testing (learn via vendor material & labs). 

OTDR basics for fiber monitoring; learn optical power metrics.


Stage D тАФ Legal labs & red/blue practice (ongoing)

Join TryHackMe / HTB lab paths and OffSec courses for hands-on in isolated environments. 

Read applied research (fiber tap papers, threat advisories) to understand advanced vectors. 


Certifications to target: Network+/Security+ (basics), OSCP / OSCP+ / GPEN / SANS courses for advanced practitioners. 


---

6) Lab blueprint тАФ рд╕реБрд░рдХреНрд╖рд┐рдд рддрд░реАрдХрд╛ (high-level, non-exploit) ЁЯзк

Build an isolated rack with: managed switch, patch panel, sample copper & fiber runs, a lab server running NSM (Zeek) and IDS (Suricata).

Create test VLANs and simulate misconfigurations (for defenders: learn to detect).

Use cable certifier (Fluke) to learn real metrics and how tampering shows up on tests.


> рдорд╣рддреНрд╡рдкреВрд░реНрдг: рдпрд╣ рд╕рдм strictly offline / lab network рдкрд░ рдХрд░реЗрдВ тАФ production рдореЗрдВ рдХрднреА рднреА рдирд╣реАрдВред Use explicit written authorization for any test beyond your own lab. 




